UDP Server :	Server accepts port number. Command to run server is 
	
	./udpserver <port_no>

MultiThreaded Server: Server accepts port number. Command to run server is 
	./multiThreaded <port_no>


UDPClient: Client accepts IP address of the server, port number  and file name as the argument. Command to run client is 

	./udpclient <IP_address> <port_no> <file_name> 

Client:  Client accepts IP address of the server, port number , Connection-Type and file name as the argument. Command to run client is 

./client <IP_address> <port_no> <connection-type> <file_name> 

NOTE : 

Connection-Type

persistant = keep-alive
non persistant= close
